The paper presents a method for performing Bayesian inference in models with conditional independence over a decentralized network of learning agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT).
